     spec%e%sig_musc  = 1.0e-6, 1.0e-6                 ! add extra mult scatt. in e Arm                                                                         
     spec%p%sig_musc  = 1.0e-6, 1.0e-6                 ! add extra mult scatt in pArm                                                                                     
     spec%e%sig_smear = 1.0e-8, 2.0e-3, 2.0e-5, 0.073                 !add extra smear. in recon eArm (Ytar, xptar(in mr), yptar(in mr), delta(in %))             
     spec%p%sig_smear = 1.0e-8, 30.0e-3, 2.0e-5, 0.073                 !add extra smear. in  recon pArm                                             
                                                                                                                                                          
----> Everything Looks OK, exept missing energy which appears a little shifted left from data                                                                                  
      **Try fitting Emiss from SIMC/DATA to determin by how much to shift either HMS or SHMS momentum                                                                                                   
      From the fit of Emiss in trial3,  Emiss_simc = 0.005469 GeV,  Emiss_data = 0.00905 GeV
      Recall, Emiss = Mtarget + Eb - E' - Ep,   E': electron energy,  Ep: proton energy
      
      **Derivatives**
      dEmiss / dEp = -1  ---> dEmiss = -dEp,      dEmiss = Emiss_simc - Emiss_data = 0.005469 - 0.00905 = -0.003581 GeV

      dEmiss / dE' = -1  ---> dEmiss = -dE'

      The corrected spectrometer momentum is:  Ep_corr = Ep + dEp = Ep - dEmiss = Ep + 0.003581,   For run 3288, Ep = 3.07767 GeV
                                                                                = 3.07767 + 0.003581 = 3.0812606 

      The corrected momentum for the HMS, is then: Pp_corr = 2.9349297